## Apple Reminders & Calendar Integration

### Reminders
- Use `@reminder(message="...", at="today/tomorrow HH:MM"|"YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM"|"+30m", list="Work", note="optional-path", priority=1|5|9, flagged=true|false)` inline in any markdown.
- Run to create/update reminders (idempotent via `@source:` marker):
  ```bash
  python3 scripts/reminders_cli.py --file "<path-to-md>" --verbose
  ```
- Notes are concise and include an inferred first step automatically.

### Calendar
- Use `@calendar(message="...", at="today/tomorrow HH:MM"|"YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM"|"+30m", duration="30m|1h|90m", calendar="Work", location="Desk", note="optional-path")`.
- Run to create/update Apple Calendar events (idempotent via `@source:` marker):
  ```bash
  python3 scripts/calendar_cli.py --file "<path-to-md>" --verbose
  ```
- Event description is concise with an inferred smallest first step.




